Hirtle, Callaghan & Co., LLC Key Developments

Hirtle Callaghan Appoints Erica Evans as Head of Client Engagement
Jul 27 17
Hirtle Callaghan announced that financial services industry veteran Erica Evans has joined the firm in the newly created role of Head of Client Engagement. In this capacity, Ms.  Evans will work closely with Hirtle Callaghan's investment officers to further the firm's client-centric model. Ms.  Evans, who most recently served as the head of Sales Strategy & Institutional Partnerships at Hartford Funds, has over 25 years of experience in the financial services industry, with expertise in sales strategy,
marketing, communications, and general management. Prior to her most recent role at Hartford Funds, Ms. Evans served as Executive Vice President and Head of Sales and Marketing at HIMCO, Hartford's asset management unit.


Hirtle Callaghan Appoints Dan Eagan as Director
Feb 16 17
Hirtle Callaghan announced it has established a presence in San Francisco with the addition of Dan Eagan who has joined the firm as a Director in its Portfolio Management Group.  In this role, Mr. Eagan will grow the firm's existing client base in Northern California and apply Hirtle Callaghan's distinctive capability in building complete, custom-designed solutions for families and institutions. He will be based at a newly established San Francisco office and will work closely with Hirtle Callaghan's Scottsdale, Arizona office to expand their presence on the West Coast. Mr.  Eagan has spent his 30-year investment career building portfolios for both institutions and family groups. He most recently served as a Managing Director at Alliance Bernstein, where he served as both the lead contact servicing institutional client relationships as well as head of the wealth management group.


Hirtle Callaghan Names Ranji Nagaswami as CEO
Aug 22 16
Hirtle Callaghan has named Ranji Nagaswami as CEO. From 2010 to 2012, Nagaswami served as chief investment adviser to the administration of Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg for New York City's $150 billion Employee Retirement Systems. Most recently, she had been operating partner and senior adviser at Corsair Capital.


